body_html:
FINALLY I GOT IT! I have no idea what and where something went wrong but you are right and there were broken link files pointing to a non existing directory with libtensorflow_demo.so.
The solution for me was to start all over with a fresh VM with enough diskspace (20GB is clearly not enough), enough memory (default is pretty low) and all cores assigned (default is 1) with the current Ubuntu 16.04 LTS and Android Studio. Also tensorflow v8.0 which came out meanwhile seems to be a bit less troublesome.

I described everything in my blog. It's in German but you'll only need the console commands anyway.
http://blog.codingyourlife.at/?page_id=1315
